en: Listed as a Historic Monument, this superb chapel dates from the 15th and 16th centuries. Rectangular in plan, it is distinguished by its flamboyant style chevet window and its western facade decorated with a portal surmounted by a large pointed arch and two geminated basket-handle doors. It is accompanied by a beautiful fountain from the end of the 17th century, also classified as a Historic Monument.
